Separating out pipeline of Lambda payload updating and infrastructure
Why do we do it?

Allows us to work on each component separately
Gives us control over each one of our components.
Changes will be less likely to affect other parts that do not need change.
Forces to reduce coupling.
Will lead to easier changes in the future
Reduces the build time


Separation of terragrunt and terraform stuff

The content in terragrunt is structured following first accounts and then environments
On the lowest level, there is a terraform.tfvars file in each directory which points at the right terraform scripts directory in the terraform folder.
The terraform folder is structured according to pipeline and lambdas.


Warum der Verzug?
Uns war nicht bekannt dass die Teilung von einem Terraform-Script bedeutet, dass wir ein Terragruntscript je Projekt ben√∂tigen.